\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. idaea} (Gand.) Lipsch., {\i Fragm. Monogr. Scorzonerae}{\b  2}: 11 (1939). Like {\b 3} but less hairy and much smaller in all its parts; stems not more than 4 cm, several, simple; leaves 3-6 cm, all basal; involucre 10-15 mm, up to 22 mm in fruit. 1800-2300 m. •{\i  Kriti.} Cr.
