\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 5. S. undulata} Vahl,{\i  Symb. Bot.}{\b  2}: 86 (1791). Glabrous or sparsely tomentose perennial 7-30 cm; rootstock vertical, 0·7-1·5 cm thick, tuberous-incrassate, oblong-cylindrical, not fibrous at apex. Stem solitary, simple or branched near the base, erect. Basal leaves 3-15 × 0·2-0·7 cm, linear to linear-lanceolate, flat, entire; cauline similar but smaller, amplexicaul. Involucre 15-25 mm. Ligules 1½-2 times as long as involucre, purplish, very rarely white. Achenes c. 12 mm, cylindrical-ellipsoid, with the ribs scabrid or rugose to squamate above, otherwise glabrous, brownish, with a paler, tubular base c. 1/5 as long as rest of achene. Pappus-hairs about as long as achene, plumose.{\i  Calcareous hills. S. Italy, Sicilia.} It Si. ({\i N. Africa.})
\par 

