\pard\f0\fs28  The European plant is subsp. {\b deliciosa }(Guss.) Maire, {\i Bull. Soc. Hist. Nat. Afr. Nord}{\b  22}: 54 (1931), with more or less glabrous leaves and scentless flowers; subsp.{\b  undulata} has hairy leaves and scented flowers. Plants of both subspecies in N. Africa often have much wider leaves.
